    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "The project intends to support the MOE for ensuring equitable and quality basic and secondary education for adolescent girls and women through formal and non-formal means of education in selected districts of Nepal. The project will focus on: ensuring comprehensive basic and secondary education (grade 6-12; ages 10-18) integrated with health issues and life skills to all adolescent girls; strengthening provisions of basic and secondary education to school dropout and out of school adolescent girls through CLCs; enhancing capacity of CLCs to mobilize and engage local level stakeholders in the promotion of girls' basic and secondary education at local level."
      },
